headline: JPMorgan Private Bank names Catania head for continental Europe
summary: JPMorgan said it had named Sarah Catania head of its private banking business for continental Europe, reporting to Pablo Garnica, chief executive of JPMorgan Private Bank for Europe, Middle East and Africa. The U.S. bank also said in an emailed note that Pietro Sala had become market manager for JPMorgan Private bank for Italy and Greece. Both Catania and Sala will continue to be based in Milan.
